description: Enforce Clerk sign-in and sign-up buttons to use modal mode and shadcn/ui components
globs: **/*.tsx,**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Clerk Auth: Always Use Modal Mode with shadcn/ui

Sign-in and sign-up buttons must always open in a modal, never navigate to a dedicated page. All trigger UI must use shadcn/ui components — never use plain HTML elements like `<button>`.

## SignInButton & SignUpButton

Always pass `mode="modal"` to `<SignInButton>` and `<SignUpButton>`, and wrap them with the shadcn/ui `<Button>` component as the child trigger.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — opens modal, uses shadcn/ui Button
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign in</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign up</Button>
</SignUpButton>

// ✅ GOOD — variant and size props are fine
<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button variant="outline" size="sm">Sign in</Button>
</SignInButton>

// ❌ BAD — plain HTML button instead of shadcn/ui Button
<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <button>Sign in</button>
</SignInButton>

// ❌ BAD — navigates to /sign-in or /sign-up page
<SignInButton>
  <Button>Sign in</Button>
</SignInButton>
```

## shadcn/ui for All Auth-Adjacent UI

Any UI surrounding auth flows — dialogs, dropdowns, menus, avatars — must also use shadcn/ui components. For example, a user menu after sign-in should use `<DropdownMenu>`, `<Avatar>`, etc. from `@/components/ui/`.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — user menu uses shadcn/ui primitives
import { DropdownMenu, DropdownMenuTrigger, DropdownMenuContent, DropdownMenuItem } from "@/components/ui/dropdown-menu";
import { Avatar, AvatarImage, AvatarFallback } from "@/components/ui/avatar";

<DropdownMenu>
  <DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
    <Avatar>
      <AvatarImage src={user.imageUrl} />
      <AvatarFallback>{user.firstName?.[0]}</AvatarFallback>
    </Avatar>
  </DropdownMenuTrigger>
  <DropdownMenuContent>
    <DropdownMenuItem>Sign out</DropdownMenuItem>
  </DropdownMenuContent>
</DropdownMenu>

// ❌ BAD — raw HTML elements for auth UI
<div onClick={openMenu}>
  <img src={user.imageUrl} />
</div>
```

## No Dedicated Auth Pages for Buttons

Do not use `<Link href="/sign-in">` or `<Link href="/sign-up">` as sign-in/sign-up triggers. These routes may still exist for direct navigation, but interactive buttons must use the modal pattern above.
